children.subject: I meant what's the workload of 162 + data 100 compared to 170 and 161? I didn't mean I'm planning to take them all at once. I'm trying to figure out what set of classes is lighter.

OHHHHHH OOPS SORRY in that case workwise 161/170 is definitely the lighter pair sorry!!

Concept wise I think 162/100 might be slightly easier?
Thanks in that case what two techs add up to about the workload of 162? I'm just trying to get a sense of how much time 162 takes.

<md>In my case, with how long my groupmates and I spent on 162 projects, I'd say that in terms of project workload for 162 it ends up to be around 61c (garcia) + 61b (hilfinger) but in terms of time spent studying for exams/digesting concepts it was more like 61c in terms of difficulty and time spent</md>

I'm no expert but I'd say that's quite a lot and kind of stretching things, even if you basically have no other obligations. 162 this semester for our group personally was a lot of work (and even with a decently reliable group, the work definitely wasn't split that evenly and I know multiple groups who spent even more time than we did). 170 isn't a lot of time work-wise but it is quite heavy conceptually, especially if maths/proofs/etc... isn't really your thing. 161 workload wise is decently light; proj2 is quite nuts though especially if you don't have a good partner. Same with 162; if you don't have a solid group (not just people you're close to, they have to pull their weight) you'll be pretty done for. Data 100, I've never taken so I can't speak as to workload wise what it'd be like.

I'm just curious why you'd want to put yourself through the ringer like this? The classes are all super enjoyable, but definitely not if you're consuming them at a breakneck speed unless you know you can handle it with prior class history. Just my 2 cents though so take it with a grain of salt!
